<font color="#FF0000">REALENE, ME, AND SOCIETY</font><br>
<tt>Mon Oct 26 22:35:49 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
I have to agree with the idea that Realene can only act in the way she has been taught. She has had a very dfferent life from many of us so her mentality is different too. It's hard for people to change and as Nancy sort of says, we can't expect her to change all of a sudden. She has to be shown or see for herself that gender roles shouldn't exist and that men and women whould be able to do the same things. In my family, my parents have three daughters and my father has always given us plenty of chances and credit to develope who we are. We do eveything from helping him renovate vacant apartments to cooking dinner and cleaning house. People may stereotype all the time based on gender, like in this case, and race. For example, I am Mexican and my parents were born and raised in Mexico. You would think that they would still be very old fashioned and traditional...Its all a matter of what you know and what you don't know. I think that as women, we need to wake up.  
